<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "2C">
<servcat sctnbr = "02" scnbr = "03">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70A2306005" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "1">
<title>
Rear Coil Spring and Spring Seat Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Be careful not to let rear axle down too much. It may cause damage to brake flexible hose, wheel speed sensor lead and parking brake cable.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A2306005001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle and remove rear wheels. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Support both ends of rear axle (1) using two floor jacks (2) to prevent it from lowering.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A230009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.740mm" ver = "02" gw = "163" gh = "124"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear shock absorber lower nut and lower washer. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A2306003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Detach lower ends of right and left rear shock absorber (1) from rear axle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Lower rear axle gradually as far down if necessary for removing rear coil spring (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear coil spring(s) (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A230007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "62.742mm" ver = "01" gw = "180" gh = "161"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear spring upper seat(s) (1) from vehicle body and rear spring lower seat(s) (2) from rear axle.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A230011.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "81.349mm" ver = "01" gw = "197" gh = "214"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<c-change/>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A2306005002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A2306006">Rear Coil Spring and Spring Seat Check</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Install spring seat in specified direction.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Otherwise, noise may occur from rear coil spring while vehicle is moving.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear spring upper seat(s) (1) to vehicle body and rear spring lower seat(s) (2) to rear axle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear coil spring(s) (3) on rear spring lower seat(s) (2) of rear axle. Place rear coil spring end (4) onto rear spring lower seat (2) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A230012.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.044mm" ver = "02" gw = "189" gh = "153"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.067in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.354in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.228in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Left side
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[u]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Upward
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[B]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Right side
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[f]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Forward
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Jack up rear axle and then install rear shock absorber (1) lower end to rear axle.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Install lower washers and tighten rear shock absorber lower nuts (2) temporarily by hand.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A230008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "62.742mm" ver = "01" gw = "180" gh = "161"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove floor jacks from rear axle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear wheels. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Lower hoist and bounce vehicle up and down several times to stabilize suspension.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten rear shock absorber lower nuts to specified torques.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
When tightening these nuts, be sure that vehicle is not on hoist and in unloaded condition.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2C003">
<t-part>
Rear shock absorber lower nut
</t-part>
<t-value1>
90
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
9.2
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
66.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
